reviewText: Strictly for Theda Bara fans.  The picture image is just fair and the direction is amazingly puritanical.  The cheating couple doesn't get past hugging one another and the woman is dressed like a salvation army worker.

This is for the Alpha 2015 DVD release. Decent enough quality, but a little dark at times. Given that this is one of only 2 or so sources for this film it is acceptable. Theda Bara, no longer the vamp in charge, still shines.

BY THE TIME THIS MOVIE WAS FILMED, THEDA BARAS STYLE OF ACTING WAS NO LONGER THE RAGE IT IS INTERESTING TO SEE HER THOUGH. I'VE HEARD SO MUCH ABOUT HER.. AND SO LITTLE IS LEFT TO WATCH. I'M STILL HOPING MORE WILL SHOW UP SOME DAY.
